Vice President Mike Pence delivered a speech in Fargo, North Dakota, highlighting the accomplishments of the Trump administration and the impact of the recent tax cuts. Pence praised the resilience and spirit of the people of North Dakota and thanked them for their support in electing President Trump. He discussed various promises made and kept by the administration, including tax cuts, rebuilding the military, securing the borders, appointing conservative judges, and combatting the opioid crisis. Pence also criticized Senator Heidi Heitkamp for voting against the tax cuts and other policies supported by the administration. He urged the audience to stay involved, spread the message of the administration's accomplishments, and pray for America's success.